              Request seasonal installment restructuring from your financier:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>CNY (Jan-Feb):</strong> Lower installments or payment holiday for 2 weeks</li>
              <li><strong>Hari Raya (Apr-May):</strong> Reduced payment during Raya month</li>
              <li><strong>Year-End (Nov-Dec):</strong> Smaller installment during 11.11/12.12 slowdown</li>
              <li><strong>Catch-Up Periods:</strong> Slightly higher payments during peak months</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. Build an Emergency Fund</h3>

          <p>
            Set aside 3 months of lorry installment payments in a separate account. This creates a buffer for unexpected delays or emergency repairs.
          </p>

